apps.title: WebDebug - Web debugging tool
apps.developer: Shanghai Dazhuo Information Technology Co., Ltd.
apps.description:
This app is a web debugging panel that can be run on iPhone, iPad, and other devices. You can conveniently debug web pages on your mobile phone. It supports local static websites, allows for testing multiple projects locally, and manages various document files.

Features:

- Debug by inputting the URL
- Debug by scanning a QR code to open the URL
- Automatically save debugging page link information to the database and record debugging time
- View console logs
- View system information
- View network requests
- View page element structure
- View cookies, localStorage, and SessionStorage
- Input JavaScript commands, e.g., alert(document.body.outerHTML);
- Inject JavaScript code snippets or plugins for web page debugging (e.g., injecting jq, vue plugins or JS code snippets), with the console displaying return values
- Web page code editing and preview function
- Code auto-suggestions for HTML, JavaScript, CSS, and content
- Keyboard extensions
- Tokenization of debugging code for easy input
- HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code input with auto-suggestions, auto-bracket matching, line numbering, code folding, and more
- Syntax error correction for HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code input, further enhancing mobile testing capabilities

Version 1.5 introduces the following new features:

1. Static server function: You can now start a local static server on your phone, supporting the creation of multiple local websites for testing. It supports WiFi, WebDAV file management, remote file downloading with decompression, direct preview of most document, video, audio, image files, and various code files on your phone.

2. Automatic injection of window.onerror code before page loading: Now, before the page loads, the application will automatically inject some code into the webpage that helps capture potential errors and print these error messages to the application's console. You can also choose to send these error reports to a backend server for further analysis and processing.

3. Show network requests when shaking the phone: When you shake your phone, the application will display the network requests made by the current page. This can help you better understand the communication between the application and the server. Additionally, you can choose to send the recorded HTTP request logs via email for further analysis.

4. jQuery-like element selector function: The application has added a feature similar to using jQuery's element selector, which means you can select and manipulate various DOM elements on the webpage more precisely, allowing for more flexible customization of page behavior and styles.

5. Code injection function: Now, you can mix HTML and JS code in the webpage being loaded. This feature supports multiple injection scenarios, meaning you can conveniently control or intercept page requests and execute custom code on the page.

6. Added dozens of code themes and code editing commands: You can easily use code auto-suggestions and customize code themes.

Unlimited Access Subscription:
- With this subscription, you can enjoy unlimited access to all features within the app.
- Subscriptions are charged weekly, monthly, or yearly, depending on the selected subscription plan.
- Payment will be charged to your iTunes account upon confirmation of purchase.
- You can turn off auto-renewal at least 24 hours before the current subscription period ends; otherwise, the subscription will automatically renew.
- The renewal fee will be charged to your account within 24 hours before the end of the current subscription period, depending on the chosen plan.
- Users can manage their subscriptions and can turn off auto-renewal in their account settings after purchase.
- Any unused portion of a free subscription trial period will be forfeited upon purchase.

Privacy Policy: https://www.dazhuogroup.com/debugweb/privacy_statement_en.php
Terms of Use: https://www.dazhuogroup.com/debugweb/terms_of_use_en.php

apps.title: Ship
apps.description:
Ship allows you code from your phone!  Simply choose the repository you'd like to edit, then prompt our Custom Language Model System (link below) with a task, changes, or a question regarding the selected Github Repository.  

Then just watch as we handle the rest! 

The changes are made on a new branch so as to not interfere with your current set up, but you can push these changes directly through the app.

We prioritized making Non-destructive changes to your Repos by having our agent push its changes to a new branch, specified by the current date. We also allow you to select an existing repo to build on top of an existing project.

We're going to be quickly adding features and want to open source our Language Model System backend in order to allow you to easily customize your own system which can do much more than just coding through an integration store!

This is the first AI Powered application that allows you to edit existing GitHub Repositories from your phone!  

Other Features:
- You can view the code within the repository that you're working with by selecting the 'Code' icon in the top right of your Chat View.
- Open Sourced Language Model System: https://github.com/LMSystems-ai/Github-Agent so you can create your own branch of our coding agent and try it out yourself! If you create something cool, we'll add it to the app and let you have access for free!

Terms of Service: https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/

apps.title: Blynk IoT
apps.description:
Trusted by over 1 million IoT developers worldwide, Blynk lets you build and customize beautiful, feature-rich apps without writing a single line of code.
Blynk solves IoT complexity at every stage with easy workflows for end-user device activation, WiFi provisioning, seamless OTA firmware updates, enterprise-grade security, and much more!

⊲ Not Just an App...

Blynk is an award-winning low-code IoT platform that supports IoT at any scale—from personal prototypes to millions of connected devices in production environments.

2024 Leader: IoT Platforms (G2)
2024 High Performer: IoT Management (G2)
2024 Momentum Leader: IoT Development Tools (G2)

Designed, developed, tested, and continuously maintained, Blynk provides the building blocks of a fully integrated cloud IoT platform software solution—loved by customers and their end-users around the world!

⊲ Here’s What You Get When You Sign Up:

Blynk.Apps: Drag-n-drop IoT app builder to build and brand feature-rich mobile apps in minutes and instantly manage devices, users, and data remotely.
Blynk.Console: A powerful web portal to manage devices, users, and organizations, perform OTA firmware updates, and handle other important business functions.
Blynk.Cloud: Cloud infrastructure needed to securely host, scale, and monitor your IoT solutions. Receive, store, and process data in real-time or at intervals. Connect to your other systems via APIs. Private server options are available.

⊲ Secure, Scalable Enterprise-Grade Infrastructure

Processing over 180 billion hardware messages monthly, Blynk provides secure, end-to-end encryption between the cloud, apps, and devices with 24/7 incident monitoring, ensuring you don’t have to worry about security.

⊲ Robust Hardware Compatibility

Supporting over 400 hardware development boards—including ESP32, Arduino, Raspberry Pi, Seeed, Particle, SparkFun, Blues, Adafruit, Texas Instruments, and more—Blynk makes it easy to connect your devices to the cloud using WiFi, Ethernet, Cellular (GSM, 2G, 3G, 4G, LTE), LoRaWAN, HTTPs, or MQTT.

⊲ Flexible Connection Options

Blynk Library: Pre-configured C++ library for low-latency, bi-directional communication.
Blynk.Edgent: Advanced features with less code for data exchange, WiFi provisioning, OTA firmware updates, and API access to apps and cloud.
Blynk.NCP: High-quality network co-processor integration for dual MCU architecture.
HTTP(s) API: Standard protocol to securely communicate and transfer data.
MQTT API: Secure, versatile two-way communication for building MQTT dashboards or panels.

⊲ What an IoT Developer Can Do with Blynk: 

• Easy Device Activation
• Device WiFi Provisioning
• Sensor Data Visualization
• Shared Access to Devices
• Data Analytics
• Remote Device Control
• Asset Tracking
• Firmware Over-the-Air (OTA) Updates
• Multi-Device Management with a Single App
• Real-Time Alerts: Send and receive push and email notifications.
• Automations: Create scenarios for one or multiple devices based on various triggers.
• Manage Multi-Level Organizations and Access to Devices
• Voice Assistant Integration: Interact with devices using Amazon Alexa and Google Home.

To use the Blynk IoT app, you must agree to our Terms of Use - https://blynk.io/tos

With Solo Code Learn AI, you’ll learn programming skills in a fun, engaging, and interactive way—all tailored to your learning style! Say goodbye to complicated coding books and hello to a more personalized, hands-on experience.  
Explore a World of Programming Languages  

Solo Code Learn AI offers extensive courses covering a wide range of programming languages and technologies. You’ll gain expertise with tools that lead to real-world applications.  
Learn JavaScript and master front-end development with our engaging tutorials.  
Build websites from scratch with Learn HTML, Learn CSS, and our intuitive HTML Editor, empowering you to craft stunning web pages.

Learn React and dominate frontend development with cutting-edge libraries.  
Prepare for future advancements with Learn Machine Learning using an intuitive AI Code Editor that makes complex algorithms simple!

Personalized Learning Pathways  
Your learning experience is unique to you. Whether you’re starting with Learn Programming for Kids, trying to grasp the basics of Learn Python 3, or exploring advanced features with the robust TypeScript Compiler, our AI customizes lessons to match your pace, goals, and interests.  
Interactive JavaScript & HTML Editors  

Our interactive JS Editor and HTML Editor bring your imagination to life. Test, debug, and see results instantly. It’s coding made simple, efficient, and fun.  
Built-In Compilers for Practical Experience  

Dive into real-world coding projects as Solo Code Learn AI allows you to test your code directly. Use the Go IDE, Python Compiler, Java IDE, and C# Compiler for hands-on practice to see immediate results and improve your coding skills.  
Engaging Content for All Ages  
Introduce coding to everyone! Whether it’s coding for kids or helping adults learn new skills, Solo Code Learn AI creates an engaging environment with quizzes, games, and real-world projects to keep the learning process entertaining.  

Whether you’re at home or on the go, Solo Code Learn AI is always with you. Seamlessly switch between learning platforms—on mobile, desktop, or online. It’s as simple as opening your browser.  

Verified Certification  
After completing any course, earn a verified Solo Code Learn AI certificate. Whether you choose Learn React, Learn Go, Learn JavaScript, or any other language, this certification adds credibility to your resume or LinkedIn profile.  
Simple Steps to Start

Use our C# IDE, Python Editor, and Go Compiler to bridge the gap between theory and practice. Write, test, and refine your code until it’s perfect.

apps.title: Azodik Utils - Developer Tools
apps.description:
Azodik Utils - Essential Developer Tools

A comprehensive collection of developer utilities designed to streamline your development workflow. All processing happens locally on your device - your data never leaves your phone.

JWT Tools

Decode JWT tokens to inspect headers, payloads, and signatures

Create and sign JWT tokens with HMAC algorithms (HS256, HS384, HS512)

Validate JWT signatures with your secret keys

Copy decoded data to clipboard with one tap

Random String Generator

Generate secure random strings for passwords, tokens, and keys

Customizable length and character sets

Copy generated strings instantly

Privacy-First Design

All data processing happens locally on your device

No data is sent to external servers

No tracking or analytics

Your secrets stay private

Built for Developers

Clean, intuitive interface

Fast and responsive

Works offline

Perfect for development, testing, and debugging

Whether you're debugging JWT tokens, generating secure strings, or need quick access to developer tools, Azodik Utils has you covered. Built by developers, for developers.

Perfect for:

API development and testing

JWT token inspection and creation

Secure password generation

Development workflow optimization

bug fixes

apps.title: iHost - HTML Live
apps.description:
iHost is a local server on your iOS device! 

You can easily share files and create a webpage all from your iOS device so that anyone on your network can see your creation. There is a built in code editor with syntax highlighting for multiple languages with a beautiful clean user interface. You can save the files with any extension meaning you can take off where you left on your computer with easy file sharing.

iHost can work with HTML Live and Web Inspect to create an array of amazing web tools that will help you code on the go to become a better developer.

Localhost was brought to you from: https://github.com/swisspol/GCDWebServer

raw_data.releaseNotes:
This app has been updated by Apple to display the Apple Watch app icon.

Improves the interaction on older devices.
Fixes an issue where the app would crash when starting the servers.
Improves server speed and reliability.
Improves code completion inside the code editor.

apps.title: QuickCode: Code Editor
apps.description:
Welcome to QuickCode, the ultimate code editor designed for users who want to code on the go with power and ease.

Featuring a sleek and intuitive interface, QuickCode offers a comprehensive set of tools tailored for both beginners and seasoned developers. Whether you're crafting a quick script or diving into a complex project, this app provides the versatility and functionality you need to bring your ideas to life.

Features:
* Syntax Highlighting: Write code with clarity and precision thanks to our advanced syntax highlighting feature, which enhances readability and reduces errors.
* Editor Themes: Customise your coding environment to suit your style with a variety of editor themes, ensuring a personalised and comfortable experience.
* Metadata Pane: Stay organised and efficient with our metadata pane, providing quick access to essential information about the file you're currently working on.
* Integration with the Files App: Seamlessly manage your projects and files using the iOS Files app integration, enabling easy access and synchronisation across your devices.
* Export to Multiple Formats: Share your code effortlessly by exporting to various file formats, ensuring compatibility with different platforms and tools.
* App Clip: Need a text editor in a pinch? Quickly install a compressed version of the app using an App Clip. 

QuickCode empowers you to code anytime, anywhere, and on any device. Download now and unleash your creativity on the go!

raw_data.releaseNotes: New In Version 1.1 - Added App Clip For iOS And iPadOS, Added New Document Dock Menu Quick Action For macOS, Allowed For More Types Of Files To Be Opened By The App, Allowed For File Metadata To Be Copied Out Of The Inspector Window, Fixed The Inspector Toolbar Overlap In iOS And iPadOS, Changed How File Attributes Are Updated To Reduce Crashing, Rebuilt For iOS And iPadOS 18 And macOS 15 Using The Xcode 16.1 SDK.

apps.title: Python Editor App
apps.description:
Introducing the ultimate Python editor for iOS!
Enjoy a powerful, easy-to-use environment for coding in Python right from your iPhone or iPad.
Whether you’re new to coding or an experienced developer, you’ll love the intuitive interface and feature-packed design that makes programming simple and efficient.

With our Python editor, you can create, edit, and run Python scripts directly on iOS.
Features include syntax highlighting, auto-indentation, and code completion, helping you write clean, error-free code.
A built-in library of reusable snippets—plus the option to create your own—makes development faster than ever.

Designed to take full advantage of iOS, the app supports Liquid Glass API for a fluid, responsive coding experience, along with multi-window support, letting you work on multiple files or scripts side by side.
Use touch gestures to navigate, split your screen to view code and console simultaneously, and keep scripts running in the background while you multitask.

And now, with the integrated OpenAI Code Assistant, you can generate, refine, and debug Python code with AI-powered suggestions—directly inside the editor.

After a 3-day free trial, a subscription unlocks the complete experience:
- OpenAI Integration (with your API key)
- OpenAI Code Assistant
- Liquid Glass API & Multi-window support
- Editor customization
- Beautiful themes
- Complete Python guidebook
- Python learning resources

apps.title: Code Runner - Compile IDE Code
apps.description:
Code Runner is a mobile coding IDE and platform (Compiler for mobile), where you can run your projects, code and learn algorithms by programming on mobile. Build and deploy your projects straight from the mobile & use of code compilations to make coding easy. Now code anytime, anywhere and on the go.

Or choose from languages like:
1. C++ : GCC compiler 6.3
2. Java : best Java Programming ide, JDK 8
3. Python : learn Python 2.7 and Python 3.
4. Php : Php Interpreter 7.0
5. Ruby : Ruby version 1.9
6. JS/NodeJS : Node.js engine 14
7. Html
8. Css
9. MongoDB
10. MySQL

Code Runner uses a Rich Text Editor supporting syntax highlighting and packed with the necessary tools to offer you all the edge that an IDE or code compiler is supposed to.

Its the fastest code compiler (IDE), coding and programming app available for ios so far.

With Code Runner one can:
Write a program/code in any of the available 50+ Programming Languages and frameworks.
Code and Debug the code, see compilation results and errors at the same time on the same screen.
Enjoy the power and ease of coding on your favourite Code Editor like Notepad++ or Sublime Text with compilation power, makes it equivalent to a powerful IDE like eclipse.
Test your problem solving skills by solving challenges from the number of algorithm based challenges available in Challenges section.
Learn Html, Css, JavaScript, Ruby programming, C Programming, Python and Java in the app along with many more programming languages.
Irrespective of your coding skills be it beginner or expert Code Runner helps you to learn code and improve your skills while in a boring lecture or whenever you feel like.

The main features include:

1. Rich Text Editor with Syntax highlighting.(Code Editor)
2. Line number, Auto indent, Autocomplete Parenthesis.
3. Undo Redo.
4. File Open/Save.
5. Custom Suggestion View.
6. Multiple Language Support.
7. User input for languages like C, C++, Java, Php, JavaScript, Node.js and others.
8. Active debug view for faster access to Output.
9. Thoroughly designed Algorithm problems to improve coding Skills and make programmers industry ready.
Size for Editor and much more!!


Disclaimer: Code Runner uses an array of strong cloud based compilers to compile the code and display output, it is the fastest one and has helped to bring app size to ~8 MB, Please don't rate low or demand offline features that is not possible here. Also instead of rating low, you can write your problems to us at support@1timetech.com that will let us help you better.

Code Runner is an online compiler, now run, compile and execute your code snippets on your own mobile devices.

Begin the journey to enhance your skills.
